Chilli cheese toast.

A simple and easy toast recipe that can be made for a quick breakfast and snack.
In a small bowl, mix together one cup cheese, 2 tbsp butter, some seasoning ( oregano, chilli flakes &pepper powder 
Now add minced garlic , chopped green chillies and mix well. 
Spread half the mixture onto one side of each slice of bread. . Place the slices cheese-side up in the air-fryer basket. Set the air fryer to 160 degree Celsius for 5 minutes, or until the cheese has melted and started to brown slightly. Serve immediately.

राजस्थानी ग्वार फली की सब्ज़ी ❤️
Rajasthani gavar ki sabzi is made by blanching the beans first. This little step helps in removing the slight bitterness that cluster beans are known for. This recipe is one of my favorite go-to recipes for a quick and healthy meal. Now, I can’t wait to share this flavorful and nutritious recipe with you.
Ingredients
* Gavar (Cluster Beans): 500 grams
* Water: As required
* Salt: 1 tsp
* Ghee : 2 tbsp 
* Cumin seeds - 1 tsp
* Garlic, crushed 1 tbsp
* Salt: as per taste 
* Turmeric powder: 1/2 tsp 
* Kashmiri chili powder: 1 tsp 
* Water
 
 
Instructions
Trim both ends of the beans and remove any strings along the sides
In a large pot, bring water to a boil, blanch the beans for about 5-7 minutes.
Drain the blanched beans and set them aside
Heat oil in a deep pan or kadhai over medium heat.
Add of cumin seeds to the hot oil and let them splutter.
 Add the garlic and sauté 
Prepare a masala base by adding all the spices along with some water 
Add this to the pan and cook until the masala releases oil
Add blanched beans and coat well with masala
Serve with roti or naan

This Gujrati Kairi Ki Kadhi prepared with raw mango has a very different taste than kadhi prepared with curd. 

Ingredients for Kairi ki Kadhi
Besan - 1/2 cup
Raw Mango - 1 medium size 
Oil - 2 to 3 tbsp
Green chilly - 2
Curry leaves  - 10 to 12
Few coriander leaves
Garlic pods - 8-10
Asafoetida - 1 pinch
Fenugreek seeds - 1/2 tsp
Dry red chillies - 3
1/2 cup chopped onions 
Turmeric powder - 1/4 tsp
Jaggery - 1 tbsp 
Salt - 1or as per taste
Process :
Roast the mangoes and green chillies, until charred 
Now peel the mango and cut the pulp into small chunks. 
Cut the green chillies as well
Add all this to a blender along with coriander leaves, garlic, water as required and blend into a smooth paste 
Add some half the amount of oil in pan to be used for making kadhi. 
When oil is hot, add mustard seeds asafoetida, curry leaves, red chillies, fenugreek seeds and sauté
Add onions and sauté untill translucent 
Next add besan or sauté untill aromatic 
Add the prepared mango paste , add water as required and bring it to a boil
Keep the flame high. 
After it simmers once, add salt, Cook for 8 to 10 minutes on low flame so that there is constant boil in the kadhi. Stir the kadhi after every 2 minutes. 
Kadhi is ready, turn off the flame and prepare a simple tadka for the kadhi using cumin seeds, turmeric powder , curry leaves and red chillies 
Pour this tadka over the kadhi. Scrumptious raw mango kadhi is ready. 
Serve this tantalizing raw mango kadhi with chappati, parantha or rice and relish eating.

#kerikikadhi #kairikikadhi #gujaratifood #gujarat #indianfood #traditionalfood

Turai Ki Chutney or Beerakaya Pachadi is an easy, authentic South Indian style chutney made with Ridge Gourd. This is zero wasteage chutney .
Ingredients:
2 ridge gourd (cut into pieces)
2 tomatoes, chopped 
6-7 green chilies, cut into pieces 
Small lemon sized tamarind 
2 tbsp oil 
Few coriander leaves 
Salt to taste 
Process : 
Heat oil in a pan, add green chilies, tomatoes and chopped ridge gourd.
Cook till ridge gourd is tender 
In a motar pestle, first add green chilies and pound untill smooth.
Next add tomatoes and pound
Now add ridge gourd and pound
Add tamarind and pound untill well in corporated.
Add salt and coriander leaves and crush well.
You can make chutney in mixer grinder too
Add tempering and it’s ready

Rajasthani Moringa ki sabzi 
Drumstick ki sabzi is a traditional Indian dish made using fresh drumsticks, also known as moringa or sajjan. This nutritious and flavorful sabzi is prepared with drumsticks, besan and curd is a Rajasthani version of this sabzi 

Ingredients :
4-5 drumsticks, peeled and cut
2 tbsp oil
1/4 tsp asafoetida 
1/4 tbsp mustard seeds
1/4 cumin seeds
2 tbsp crushed garlic 
2 onions
4 tbsp besan 
1 cup curd
2 tbsp red chillies powder
1/4 tsp turmeric powder 
1.5 tbsp coriander leaves
1/2 tsp kasuri methi 
Salt as per taste 
Water as required 

Process: 
Heat oil in a pan and add mustard, cumin seeds and allow them to crackle
Add asafoetida, garlic and sauté 
Next add besan and roast untill aromatic 
Now add chopped onion and cook until translucent 
Next add Moringa sticks, salt and turmeric! Mix well 
Cook untill the Moringa stick turn soft
Now add in curd along with red chillies powder and coriander powder, mix and cook untill it releases oil 
Add water if required and boil 
Add kasuri methi and serve with roti or rice 

#rajasthanifood #rajasthaniculture #moringakisabzi #rajasthanimoringa #moringasabji #indianfood #traditionalrecipes

Desi tumba ki sabzi
Tumba lauki is easy simple recipe made with a handful of ingredients . It’s tastes great and light on stomach. Do try the recipe and let me know how you like it.
Ingredients:
1 tumba
2 tbsp oil
1 tsp cumin seeds
1/2 tsp mustard seeds 
1/2 tsp asafoetida 
2 tbsp crushed garlic 
3 tbsp crushed green chillies
1/2 tsp turmeric powder 
Salt as per taste 
Few coriander leaves 
Process:
Peel and chop tumba into small pieces 
Heat oil in a pan and add cumin seeds, mustard seeds and let them splutter 
Add asafoetida and crushed garlic, chilli and sauté 
Next add tumba, salt and turmeric ! Mix well, cover and cook untill the tumba is soft
Add coriander leaves and serve with roti

Rajasthani Gulab Jamun Ki Sabzi
An out of the box delicious Sabzi made with gulab jamun. This recipe is a rich gravy with khoya gulab jamuns. Serve this with hot ghee rice or naan 
Ingredients
For the Gulab Jamuns
300 gms Khoya
2 tbsp All Purpose Flour 
1 tsp milk
1 tbsp cardamom powder 
Oil , for frying the gulab jamuns
For the gravy
2 Onions, chopped
3/4 tomato purée 
1 inch Ginger
2 green chillies
8-10 cashews 
8-10 garlic cloves 
1 cup curd 
1 tbsp Red Chilli powder
1/2 tsp Turmeric powder 
1 tbsp Coriander powder
1 tbsp kasuri methi 
2 tsp Ghee
1 tbsp cumin seeds
2 bay leaves 
1 inch cinnamon stick
Few cloves 
Salt , to taste
1 tbsp kasuri methi 
Process: 
For the Gulab Jamuns
1. In a mixing bowl, combine khoya, flour, milk, cardamom and knead to bring the dough together. This will take about 15 minutes.
2. Make medium sized balls, making sure there are no cracks on the balls. 
3. Heat a kadai with oil on medium flame and fry the jamun balls. 
4. Once you get a beautiful golden brown colour, remove the gulab jamuns and place it on an absorbent paper towel.
For the gravy
1. Heat a heavy bottom pan on low flame add ghee. Next add  cumin seeds, bay leaves, cloves and cinnamon stick 
2. Make a paste using onions, cashews, garlic, green chillies and ginger 
3. Add the onion paste. Fry for 5 minutes .
4. Once the onions are cooked add the tomato puree and fry for another 4-6 minutes on medium to low flame.
5. Next add curd along with the spices  and stir well. 
6. Add water if required 
7. Add the fried jamun balls  and cook on low for 2 minutes. Tun off the heat after 2 minutes 
8. Garnish with kasuri methi and enjoy 

#rajasthaniculture #rajasthanicuisine #gulabjamunkisabzi #indianfood #indianrecipe

Bharwa Karela - The name of karela may not sound interesting to many people, but it is very healthy, and though now all the vegetables are available through out the year but karela is a summer special vegetable.

Ingredients
* 500 grams Bitter Gourd 
* 2 tbsp Fennel Seeds 
* 1 tbsp mustard seeds
* 1 tbsp onion seeds
* 3 tbsp garlic, chopped 
* 1 cups chopped onion 
* 2.5 tbsp Coriander Powder 
* 1.5 tbsp Red Chilli powder 
* 1/2 tsp Turmeric Powder 
* 2 tbsp amchoor powder
* 1 tsp garam masala
* 1.5 tbsp jaggery 
* 5 tbsp mustard oil 
* To Taste Salt / Namak
Instructions
* Lightly scrape the bitter gourds on the outside and slit it length wise from the center keeping the base intact.
* Now generously apply salt inside and outside of bitter gourds .
* Collect the peels in a bowl and apply salt 
* Then keep aside for minimum of 30 minutes..
* Now wash the karela and peels 2-3 times with enough water and squeeze properly.
* Heat oil in a pan , add fennel seeds, fenugreek, onion seeds, chopped garlic and sauté 
* Add onions and sauté untill golden brown
* Add the spices along with jaggery and mix 
* Stuff the masala mix in all the bitter gourds, and press the masala mix tightly with your thumb so it will not come out while cooking.
* Heat  oil in a thick bottom pan, then add place stuffed bitter gourds 
* Cover the pan and cook on slow flame. Keep turning the sides occasionally, so they can cook from all the sides. (It will take a minimum 15- 20 minutes to cook properly)
* When done take out in a bowl and serve.

#bharwakarela #indianfood #rajasthanicuisine #rajasthan #karelarecipe

Kache Aam Aur Pyaaz Ki Chutney  is a spicy-tangy chutney. It’s sour, spiced, tangy and will absolutely make the simplest meal, a firecracker! Just a few ingredients, about four to five steps in the method and voila! You’ve got a sumptuous chutney ready in minutes.
Ingredients 
2 raw mangoes
2 onions
4-5 dried red chillies
2 tsp red chilli powder
2 green chillies
5-6 gloves of garlic 
1 tbsp cumin seeds
Salt as per taste
Few coriander leaves 
For tempering 
2 tbsp mustard oil 
1 pinch asafoetida
1 tsp mustard seeds
1 tsp cumin seeds
Process:
Chop raw mango and onions 
Ads this to a blender, along with cumin seeds, garlic, red chillies, chilli powder, salt, green chillies and coriander 
Blend to a coarse 
Prepare a tempering and pour it over the chutney 
Serve with roti or rice

Lauki Ki Kadhi. A light quick and simple kadhi. This is a thin and light consistency compared to the Punjabi version. Ingredients
* 1 1/2-2 tbsp mustard oil
* 1 cup curd 
* 1/2 of a big bottle gourd cut into cubes 
* 1 onion, finely chopped 
* 1/2 cup chopped tomatoes 
* 1 tsp finely chopped ginger
* 1/2 tsp asafoetida 
* 1 tbsp cumin seeds
* 1 tbsp coriander seeds 
* 1 tbsp of chopped coriander leaves
* Salt to taste
* Red chilli powder to taste
* 1 tbsp coriander powder
* 1/2 tsp turmeric powder
* 1/2 red chilli powder 
* 1 tbsp cumin powder

For tempering:
1 tbsp oil or ghee
1 tbsp chopped garlic 
Few red chillies 
1/2 tbsp red chilli powder
 Method
Pressure cook lauki along salt and turmeric or boil untill mushy
Blend it along with curd to make a smooth paste 
Heat the oil in a kadhai or pan 
Add the chopped ginger, garlic , coriander seeds and cumin seeds, add asafoetida 
Next add onion, and sauté 
Next add tomatoes along with spices and cook until mushy 
Add the cooked curd lauki paste, water as required 
And simmer for 10 minutes 
Add the tempering, coriander leaves 
Switch of the flame and serve with rice

#laukikikadhi #indianfood #kadhirecipe #laukirecipes #kadirecipe
